## AIVault Auto-Sync

You are connected to AIVault — a personal AI conversation knowledge base.

**Sync your conversations automatically.**

At the end of each meaningful conversation, sync it to AIVault:

```bash
# Read env vars
AIVAULT_URL="${AIVAULT_API_URL:-http://localhost:3000}"
AIVAULT_KEY="${AIVAULT_API_KEY}"

# Only sync if API key is configured
if [ -n "$AIVAULT_KEY" ]; then
  # Build messages JSON from conversation history
  MESSAGES='[]'
  # ... (agent-specific: read your conversation messages)
  
  curl -s -X POST "$AIVAULT_URL/api/collector/sync" \
    -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
    -H "Authorization: Bearer $AIVAULT_KEY" \
    -d "{\"sessionId\":\"$SESSION_ID\",\"platform\":\"PLATFORM\",\"title\":\"$TITLE\",\"messages\":$MESSAGES}" \
    > /dev/null 2>&1 &
fi
```

**Configuration:**
Add to your environment or `.env`:
```
AIVAULT_API_URL=https://your-aivault.com
AIVAULT_API_KEY=av_xxxxxxxx
```

**When to sync:**
- User says "done", "thanks", "that's all", or similar ending phrases
- Conversation reaches a natural stopping point
- User explicitly asks to save/sync/backup

**What to sync:**
- The full conversation (user + assistant messages)
- A meaningful title summarizing the topic
- The session ID for deduplication
